---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy — XYXP"
  description="How XYXP collects, uses, and protects your personal data."
>
  <Nav />

  <main class="legal-page">
    <div class="legal-container">

      <div class="legal-header">
        <p class="legal-eyebrow">Legal</p>
        <h1 class="legal-title">Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="legal-date">Last updated: April 8, 2026</p>
      </div>

      <div class="legal-body">

        <p class="intro">
          XY Axis ("we", "us", or "our") operates XYXP, a microlearning platform designed to help
          organisations run competitive, quiz-based training for their teams. This Privacy Policy
          explains how we collect, use, store, and protect your information when you use the XYXP
          platform. By creating an account or using XYXP, you agree to the practices described here.
        </p>

        <section>
          <h2>1. Who We Are</h2>
          <p>
            XYXP is operated by XY Axis. For any privacy-related questions or requests, please
            contact us at <a href="mailto:hello@xyxp.co.uk">hello@xyxp.co.uk</a>.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>

          <h3>Account Information</h3>
          <p>
            When you register for XYXP, we collect your full name, email address, and a securely
            hashed password. Administrators may also provide the name of their organisation.
          </p>

          <h3>Platform Activity</h3>
          <p>
            To provide the core service, we collect data about your participation on the platform,
            including quiz attempts and scores, XP (experience points) earned, challenge completion
            timestamps, leaderboard rankings, and group or team membership within your organisation.
          </p>

          <h3>Technical Data</h3>
          <p>
            We automatically collect certain technical information when you access XYXP, including
            your IP address, browser type and version, device type, and general usage patterns such
            as pages visited and session duration. This data is used solely for security, debugging,
            and platform improvement.
          </p>

          <h3>Communications</h3>
          <p>
            If you contact us directly or receive invite emails, we retain the content of those
            communications to assist with your query.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>3. How We Use Your Information</h2>
          <p>We use the information we collect to:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Provide, operate, and maintain the XYXP platform</li>
            <li>Authenticate your identity and manage your account</li>
            <li>Display leaderboards and track competitive progress within your organisation</li>
            <li>Send account-related emails (invitations, password resets, confirmations)</li>
            <li>Generate quiz content using AI tools on behalf of administrator accounts</li>
            <li>Analyse usage to improve platform features and performance</li>
            <li>Comply with legal obligations and enforce our Terms of Service</li>
          </ul>
          <p>We do not sell your personal data. We do not use your data for advertising.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>4. Data Sharing and Third-Party Services</h2>
          <p>
            We use a limited number of trusted third-party services to operate XYXP. Each service
            is bound by appropriate data processing agreements.
          </p>

          <div class="third-party-list">
            <div class="third-party-item">
              <p class="third-party-name">Supabase</p>
              <p>
                Our database and authentication provider. Your account credentials, profile data,
                quiz results, and platform activity are stored in Supabase's secure infrastructure.
                Supabase is SOC 2 Type II certified.
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="third-party-item">
              <p class="third-party-name">Resend</p>
              <p>
                Our transactional email provider, used to deliver account invitations, password
                resets, and other platform notifications.
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="third-party-item">
              <p class="third-party-name">Anthropic (Claude)</p>
              <p>
                Used by administrator accounts to generate quiz question content via AI. Only the
                subject matter or topic provided by the administrator is sent to Anthropic. No
                personal learner data is shared with Anthropic.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <p>
            We do not share your personal information with any other third parties, except where
            required by law or in connection with a business transfer, in which case we will
            notify you.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>5. Data Retention</h2>
          <p>
            We retain your personal data for as long as your account is active or as needed to
            provide the service. If you request account deletion, we will remove your personal
            information within 30 days, subject to any legal retention obligations.
          </p>
          <p>
            Aggregated, anonymised usage statistics that cannot identify you may be retained
            indefinitely for platform analytics.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>6. Your Rights</h2>
          <p>
            Depending on where you are located, you may have the following rights regarding your
            personal data:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Access</strong> — request a copy of the personal data we hold about you</li>
            <li><strong>Rectification</strong> — ask us to correct inaccurate or incomplete data</li>
            <li><strong>Erasure</strong> — request deletion of your personal data</li>
            <li><strong>Restriction</strong> — ask us to limit how we process your data</li>
            <li><strong>Portability</strong> — receive your data in a structured, machine-readable format</li>
            <li><strong>Objection</strong> — object to certain types of processing</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            To exercise any of these rights, please email
            <a href="mailto:hello@xyxp.co.uk">hello@xyxp.co.uk</a>. We will respond within 30 days.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>7. Cookies</h2>
          <p>
            XYXP uses session cookies and local storage to maintain your authenticated session.
            These are strictly necessary for the platform to function and cannot be disabled. We
            do not use advertising or tracking cookies.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>8. Security</h2>
          <p>
            We employ industry-standard measures including encrypted data transmission (TLS/HTTPS),
            hashed password storage, and role-based access controls. However, no method of
            transmission over the internet is 100% secure. If you believe your account has been
            compromised, please contact us immediately at
            <a href="mailto:hello@xyxp.co.uk">hello@xyxp.co.uk</a>.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>9. Children's Privacy</h2>
          <p>
            XYXP is intended for use by organisations and their employees or members. The platform
            is not directed at individuals under the age of 16. If you become aware that a minor
            has provided us with personal data without appropriate consent, please contact us and
            we will remove that information promptly.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>10. Changes to This Policy</h2>
          <p>
            We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. When we do, we will revise the
            "Last updated" date at the top of this page. For material changes, we will notify
            account holders by email. Continued use of XYXP after changes are posted constitutes
            your acceptance of the revised policy.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>11. Contact Us</h2>
          <p>If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us:</p>
          <div class="contact-card">
            <p class="contact-label">XY Axis</p>
            <p><a href="mailto:hello@xyxp.co.uk">hello@xyxp.co.uk</a></p>
          </div>
        </section>

      </div>
    </div>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  .legal-page {
    flex: 1;
    overflow-y: auto;
    padding: 64px 48px 80px;
  }

  .legal-container {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  /* ── Header ──────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .legal-header {
    padding-bottom: 40px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #e4e4e7;
    margin-bottom: 56px;
  }

  .legal-eyebrow {
    font-family: 'Space Grotesk', sans-serif;
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 2px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #0047ab;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }

  .legal-title {
    font-family: 'Newsreader', serif;
    font-weight: 400;
    font-size: clamp(36px, 4vw, 48px);
    line-height: 1.1;
    color: #1a1c1c;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }

  .legal-date {
    font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
    font-size: 14px;
    color: #71717a;
  }

  /* ── Body ─────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .legal-body {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 40px;
  }

  .intro {
    font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
    font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 26px;
    color: #71717a;
  }

  section {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 12px;
  }

  section h2 {
    font-family: 'Space Grotesk', sans-serif;
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 15px;
    letter-spacing: 0.2px;
    color: #1a1c1c;
  }

  section h3 {
    font-family: 'Space Grotesk', sans-serif;
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 1.1px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #71717a;
    margin-top: 8px;
  }

  section p {
    font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
    font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 26px;
    color: #3f3f46;
  }

  section ul {
    list-style: disc;
    padding-left: 20px;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 8px;
  }

  section li {
    font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
    font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 24px;
    color: #3f3f46;
  }

  section a {
    color: #0047ab;
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
  }

  section a:hover { color: #003a8c; }

  /* ── Third-party cards ────────────────────────────────── */
  .third-party-list {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 12px;
  }

  .third-party-item {
    background: #fff;
    border: 1px solid #e4e4e7;
    border-radius: 6px;
    padding: 16px 20px;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 6px;
  }

  .third-party-name {
    font-family: 'Space Grotesk', sans-serif;
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 12px;
    letter-spacing: 0.6px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #1a1c1c;
  }

  /* ── Contact card ─────────────────────────────────────── */
  .contact-card {
    background: #fff;
    border: 1px solid #e4e4e7;
    border-radius: 6px;
    padding: 20px 24px;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 6px;
  }

  .contact-label {
    font-family: 'Space Grotesk', sans-serif;
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 1.1px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #71717a;
  }

  /* ── Responsive ───────────────────────────────────────── */
  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .legal-page { padding: 40px 24px 64px; }
  }
</style>
